# Schema & Seed File Conventions

## When Creating New Tables

Always place table SQL files in the correct domain folder:

| Domain | Location | Example |
|--------|----------|---------|
| Master tables (global) | `server/schema/disposition/` | `industries.sql`, `dispo_types_master.sql` |
| Tenant tables | `server/schema/disposition/` | `dispositions.sql`, `dialing_sets.sql` |
| User/Auth tables | `server/schema/user/` | `user.sql`, `refresh_token.sql` |
| RBAC tables | `server/schema/rbac/` | `role.sql`, `permission.sql` |
| Contact tables | `server/schema/contact/` | (future) |
| New domains | `server/schema/<domain>/` | Create new folder |

**After creating a table**, update the relevant `run_all.sql` if it exists.

## When Creating Seed Data

Always place seed files in the correct subfolder:

| Seed Type | Location |
|-----------|----------|
| System/Platform data | `server/schema/seeds/01_system/` |
| RBAC (permissions, roles) | `server/schema/seeds/02_rbac/` |
| Master reference data | `server/schema/seeds/03_master/` |
| New seed categories | `server/schema/seeds/0X_<category>/` |

**After creating a seed file**, update `server/schema/seeds/run_all_seeds.sql` to include it.

## When Creating Migrations

Place migration files in `server/schema/migrations/` with naming:
- `001_description.sql`, `002_description.sql`, etc.

## Table Schema Requirements

All master tables must include:
- `is_active TINYINT(1) NOT NULL DEFAULT 1`
- `is_deleted TINYINT(1) NOT NULL DEFAULT 0`
- `deleted_at TIMESTAMP NULL DEFAULT NULL`
- `created_by`, `updated_by` (foreign keys to users)
- `created_at`, `updated_at` timestamps

All tenant tables must include:
- `tenant_id BIGINT UNSIGNED NOT NULL`
- `is_deleted TINYINT(1) NOT NULL DEFAULT 0`
- `deleted_at TIMESTAMP NULL DEFAULT NULL`

## Checklist for New Features

When adding a new feature with database tables:
1. ✅ Create table schema in correct folder
2. ✅ Update `run_all.sql` if exists
3. ✅ Create seed data if needed
4. ✅ Update `run_all_seeds.sql`
5. ✅ Create migration if altering existing tables
